cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) due to its focus on machine learning problems in natural language that require the characterization of linguistic context. The use of multiplicative weight-update algorithms and the evaluation of the algorithm's performance against other systems in the literature also suggest a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The problem of context-sensitive spelling correction may also involve information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE) for feature extraction and classification.
